.TH "kbuffer_curr_size" 9 "kbuffer_curr_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kbuffer_curr_size \- return the size of the entire record
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kbuffer_curr_size
.BI "(struct kbuffer *kbuf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kbuf" 12
The kbuffer to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the size of the entire record (meta data and payload)
of the current event.
